      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T13:49:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Example:\n\nA system with a superchassis (chassis1) and a subchassis (chassis2):\n\nchassis1 - containing -\u003e fan1\nchassis1 - cooled_by -\u003e fan1\n\nchassis2 - cooled_by -\u003e fan1\n\nResulting fan collections with your suggestion:\n\nchassis1: [fan1]\nchassis2: [fan1]\n\nWhen allowing per-chassis detection of code path, `fan1` resource would appear in 2 separate fan collections which is against the interpretation stated in Redfish forum.\n\nWith this implementation, when forming the response for a fan collection for chassis2, we must already know the entire association layout.\n\nIf someone wants to use this new code i don\u0027t see why they cannot configure all the chassis and fans within their system to align with that.",
